Language: en

00:00:03.830 --> 00:00:06.120
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: Good morning again everyone.

00:00:06.120 --> 00:00:07.120
My name is Reto Meier.

00:00:07.120 --> 00:00:08.120
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: And I'm Ian Ni-Lewis.

00:00:08.120 --> 00:00:11.559
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: And it's time for the developers
at traveling planning and booking apps to

00:00:11.559 --> 00:00:12.559
strike back.

00:00:12.559 --> 00:00:15.240
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: You know, every week we spend
a lot of time talking about other people's

00:00:15.240 --> 00:00:20.140
apps, not always nicely, so today's show is
a chance for the developers of the apps we

00:00:20.140 --> 00:00:21.170
tore apart during the app clinic-

00:00:21.170 --> 00:00:25.720
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: And put together again during
Android Design In Action, humpty dumpty style.

00:00:25.720 --> 00:00:28.170
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: to give us a piece of their
mind.

00:00:28.170 --> 00:00:30.470
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: In last week's App Clinic we
looked at these five travel planning apps.

00:00:30.470 --> 00:00:35.020
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: We learned a few things, not
the least of which is, don't trust Daniel

00:00:35.020 --> 00:00:36.370
Pham with the sound board.

00:00:36.370 --> 00:00:38.780
Also, five apps is too many to review.

00:00:38.780 --> 00:00:42.659
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: We also learned that people
found our featureless, black, void background

00:00:42.659 --> 00:00:44.330
too stark reminder of their own mortality.

00:00:44.330 --> 00:00:46.680
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: Right, did we have that featureless
black void or are we not doing that anymore

00:00:46.680 --> 00:00:47.680
at all?

00:00:47.680 --> 00:00:52.510
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: I think that, I don't know,
do we still have the featureless black background?

00:00:52.510 --> 00:00:54.150
I think we're not doing that at all anymore.

00:00:54.150 --> 00:00:55.280
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: Okay, yeah.

00:00:55.280 --> 00:00:56.651
I'll take the blame on that one.

00:00:56.651 --> 00:01:01.019
Our producers asked me to come up with something
that reflected who I was as a person and this

00:01:01.019 --> 00:01:02.019
is what I came up with.

00:01:02.019 --> 00:01:06.180
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: In terms of apps themselves,
we came up with the following prescriptions.

00:01:06.180 --> 00:01:09.910
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: We want the apps to be consistent
with the design guide.

00:01:09.910 --> 00:01:10.910
Don't we always want that?

00:01:10.910 --> 00:01:12.200
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: We pretty much always want that.

00:01:12.200 --> 00:01:13.200
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: Indeed we do.

00:01:13.200 --> 00:01:16.211
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: In fact, that's why Roman keeps
dialing in to all of our shows, is just to

00:01:16.211 --> 00:01:18.860
make sure that we keep pounding on that dead
horse.

00:01:18.860 --> 00:01:19.860
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: Is that why?

00:01:19.860 --> 00:01:20.860
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: I'm pretty sure.

00:01:20.860 --> 00:01:21.980
It's not for the entertainment.

00:01:21.980 --> 00:01:22.980
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: No, it's not.

00:01:22.980 --> 00:01:26.070
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: We also wanna make sure that
these apps in particular are location aware.

00:01:26.070 --> 00:01:30.690
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: We wanted them to integrate
with our digital life, you know, I use Gmail

00:01:30.690 --> 00:01:36.790
and G Calendar for everything, other people
use, people use Facebook or different types

00:01:36.790 --> 00:01:41.730
of things and integration with the things
that I use to organize my life is an absolute

00:01:41.730 --> 00:01:42.730
must for travel apps.

00:01:42.730 --> 00:01:45.370
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: Absolutely, and, you know, as
far as that goes, we wanna make sure that

00:01:45.370 --> 00:01:47.450
you can plan your entire trip using the same
app.

00:01:47.450 --> 00:01:51.500
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: Including all those damn guided
tours that my wife likes to go on.

00:01:51.500 --> 00:01:52.500
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: Absolutely.

00:01:52.500 --> 00:01:54.000
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: Buses full of Chinese people.

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:55.000
[Laughter]

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:58.070
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: And finally, we wanna make sure
that we can complete the entire transaction

00:01:58.070 --> 00:01:59.070
on the device.

00:01:59.070 --> 00:02:02.720
So we don't wanna get thrown off to a website
or a web view, if at all possible we want

00:02:02.720 --> 00:02:03.780
that to all happen.

00:02:03.780 --> 00:02:07.490
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: And I should mention, just
in case I sounded racist, my wife is Chinese

00:02:07.490 --> 00:02:08.840
and we take the Chinese tours, that's why.

00:02:08.840 --> 00:02:09.840
[Laughter]

00:02:09.840 --> 00:02:10.840
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: That makes a lot of sense.

00:02:10.840 --> 00:02:11.840
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: Right, exactly.

00:02:11.840 --> 00:02:12.840
I didn't want that to sound bad.

00:02:12.840 --> 00:02:17.360
Alright, so let's go ahead and take a look
at who we've got with us today.

00:02:17.360 --> 00:02:19.420
We've got Goran Kukurin is it?

00:02:19.420 --> 00:02:20.910
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: I hope so.

