app didn't do a lot of the things that the

00:03:02.760 --> 00:03:03.760
other apps did.

00:03:03.760 --> 00:03:04.760
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: We were a little unfair, actually.

00:03:04.760 --> 00:03:05.790
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: It was totally unfair.

00:03:05.790 --> 00:03:10.680
So I'm glad that Goran is here to tell us
just how unfair we were in person.

00:03:10.680 --> 00:03:15.930
So, hopefully we've got Goran available on
the hangout.

00:03:15.930 --> 00:03:19.470
If we can put him on screen as well that would
be awesome.

00:03:19.470 --> 00:03:23.300
Nice, that's kind of a funky effect with that
background.

00:03:23.300 --> 00:03:25.380
Hey, Goran, welcome to the show.

00:03:25.380 --> 00:03:27.700
I see you've got a partner with you as well.

00:03:27.700 --> 00:03:30.970
If you guys want to spend a little bit of
time, just introduce yourselves, tell us who

00:03:30.970 --> 00:03:33.290
you are and a little bit about Worldwide Webcams.

00:03:33.290 --> 00:03:35.780
&gt;&gt;Goran: Okay, Hi Reto.

00:03:35.780 --> 00:03:46.520
My partner is actually my so, one of my two
sons who both was involved in developing the

00:03:46.520 --> 00:03:48.020
Worldscope Webcams.

00:03:48.020 --> 00:03:53.349
My background is; I was a computer engineer
long time ago.

00:03:53.349 --> 00:03:55.140
I started with ZX Sinclair 81.

00:03:55.140 --> 00:03:56.209
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: Nice.

00:03:56.209 --> 00:03:57.209
[Laughter]

00:03:57.209 --> 00:03:58.349
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: As did I.

00:03:58.349 --> 00:04:07.710
&gt;&gt;Goran: Okay, but, now for years I work professionally
work in IT and development but everything

00:04:07.710 --> 00:04:16.579
started when I received an Android phone for
my birthday two years ago.

00:04:16.579 --> 00:04:24.690
And with local competition, Android development
competition, and then I decided to come back

00:04:24.690 --> 00:04:28.500
and start to learn Android.

00:04:28.500 --> 00:04:38.330
Java and C was already known to me but Java
and [unintelligible] was something new and,

00:04:38.330 --> 00:04:45.300
together with my team, we started looking
for idea for developing profession.

00:04:45.300 --> 00:04:55.520
We did some research on the web on other up
source and then we decided to develop Worldscope

00:04:55.520 --> 00:05:01.860
Webcams and in about one month of half time
working we're now straight time, Worldscope

00:05:01.860 --> 00:05:03.139
was born.

00:05:03.139 --> 00:05:14.150
It was version 1.0 and now, three years later,
we have almost half a million downloads and

00:05:14.150 --> 00:05:27.069
we are looking forward to hearing feedback
from you, from Nick, from Roman and I think

00:05:27.069 --> 00:05:30.379
the new version will come in the next weeks.

00:05:30.379 --> 00:05:31.650
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: Oh, very cool.

00:05:31.650 --> 00:05:34.789
So you've got a new version queued up, ready
to go next week?

00:05:34.789 --> 00:05:35.860
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: Excellent.

00:05:35.860 --> 00:05:36.930
&gt;&gt;Goran: Next weeks.

00:05:36.930 --> 00:05:38.360
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: Next weeks.

00:05:38.360 --> 00:05:41.520
[Laughter]
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: That's a very important clarification.

00:05:41.520 --> 00:05:42.520
That's really cool.

00:05:42.520 --> 00:05:48.909
Now, I wanted to make sure that we got a chance
to bring Roman up because I know that, at

00:05:48.909 --> 00:05:54.490
one point, Worldscope Webcams was gonna be
one of the app Android Design In Action candidates

00:05:54.490 --> 00:05:56.629
which I think got traded out at the last minute.

00:05:56.629 --> 00:06:01.259
So, I do hope that Roman's got some feedback
that he can share with these guys.

00:06:01.259 --> 00:06:02.559
You're up, Roman.

00:06:02.559 --> 00:06:05.020
&gt;&gt;Roman Nurik: Am I on the screen?

00:06:05.020 --> 00:06:06.020
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: You are.

00:06:06.020 --> 00:06:08.369
&gt;&gt;Roman Nurik: I guess I'm on the screen.

00:06:08.369 --> 00:06:14.409
So we actually, Nick and I provided Goran
some feedback, separately, on Google Plus.

00:06:14.409 --> 00:06:20.379
A bunch of the feedback is really around styling,
basic visual things.

00:06:20.379 --> 00:06:27.400
Like, one of the biggest points of ours was,
there's a case when you had the map, right,

00:06:27.400 --> 00:06:31.860
you had the map in the background and then
images just kind of floating, I guess thumbnails

00:06:31.860 --> 00:06:38.430
of the webcam floating over the map and it
didn't seem like there was a purpose, or it

00:06:38.430 --> 00:06:43.789
didn't seem like there was a strong, kind
of, cue as to what was going on there so we

00:06:43.789 --> 00:06:47.669
had made some suggestions like maybe having
a background behind those images would give

00:06:47.669 --> 00:06:52.479
a feel of a swipeable surface where you can
go up and down, like, that's actually a list

00:06:52.479 --> 00:06:53.939
view.

00:06:53.939 --> 00:06:57.080
So we made a couple suggestions there, we
made a couple suggestions, like you guys said,

00:06:57.080 --> 00:07:00.789
around, I think it was last week in the App
Clinic you mentioned like around the search

00:07:00.789 --> 00:07:01.879
icon and things like that.

00:07:01.879 --> 00:07:07.050
So we made a couple suggestions, in general,
around visual styling and things like that.

00:07:07.050 --> 00:07:08.050
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: Cool.

00:07:08.050 --> 00:07:12.659
&gt;&gt;Roman Nurik: But one of the reasons that
we made the switch at the last minute was

00:07:12.659 --> 00:07:18.060
that, I think it was just, you know, a little
easier for us to just think of how we can

00:07:18.060 --> 00:07:25.580
redesign a trip advisor and Worldscope Webcams
is such a unique app that we can't just, you

00:07:25.580 --> 00:07:30.500
know, jump in and redesign it for you, that's
part of the interesting problem of designing

00:07:30.500 --> 00:07:35.360
such a unique app is think of a way to be
unique and present the awesome amounts of

00:07:35.360 --> 00:07:40.520
content you have, you know, the thumbnails,
the maps and everything, in a unique way and

00:07:40.520 --> 00:07:41.699
we didn't wanna do that for you.

00:07:41.699 --> 00:07:42.699
[Laughter]

00:07:42.699 --> 00:07:43.949
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: Yeah because you didn't wanna
take away the magic, right?

00:07:43.949 --> 00:07:44.949
Not because it was too hard work.

00:07:44.949 --> 00:07:45.949
&gt;&gt;Roman Nurik: Yeah.

00:07:45.949 --> 00:07:46.949
[Laughter]

00:07:46.949 --> 00:07:47.949
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: Cause Roman's a hard worker.

00:07:47.949 --> 00:07:48.949
&gt;&gt;Roman Nurik: Exactly.

00:07:48.949 --> 00:07:49.949
[Laughter]

00:07:49.949 --> 00:07:52.830
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: You know, one thing we said,
I remember, last week about Worldwide Webcams

00:07:52.830 --> 00:07:58.969
was is it seemed like it would work best in
conjunction with one of these other apps and

00:07:58.969 --> 00:08:03.509
I wouldn't wanna say make it a plugin on another
app because we dinged a lot of apps for having

00:08:03.509 --> 00:08:04.509
too many plug ins.

00:08:04.509 --> 00:08:05.509
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: Yep.

00:08:05.509 --> 00:08:10.369
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: But this is one of those times
when I really wish we had a, you know, intent

00:08:10.369 --> 00:08:16.430
registry or something where you'd say any
travel apps that wants to use the Worldwide

00:08:16.430 --> 00:08:24.249
Webcams functionality could fire off an intent
and get that kind of additional trip planning

00:08:24.249 --> 00:08:25.249
feature.

00:08:25.249 --> 00:08:28.649
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: Absolutely, Goran, is that something
that is already available in your app or is

00:08:28.649 --> 00:08:32.970
this something you'd consider doing so building
an intent that a third party app developer

00:08:32.970 --> 00:08:37.910
could use to launch your app and display webcam
for, you know, a particular location?

00:08:37.910 --> 00:08:41.530
&gt;&gt;Goran: Yes, actually it is.

00:08:41.530 --> 00:08:49.600
Worldscope webcams is reacting on geo intent
so when it receives coordinates then you will

00:08:49.600 --> 00:08:53.250
get a list of webcams found near the specified
location.

00:08:53.250 --> 00:08:55.480
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: That's really cool.

00:08:55.480 --> 00:08:57.290
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: Yeah, that is great.

00:08:57.290 --> 00:08:58.290
Okay.

00:08:58.290 --> 00:08:59.750
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: I like that a lot.

00:08:59.750 --> 00:09:02.050
That's exactly the way that you should be
doing things like that.

00:09:02.050 --> 00:09:08.080
So, hopefully some of the other developers
building these travel booking apps will take

00:09:08.080 --> 00:09:09.080
a look at that.

00:09:09.080 --> 00:09:11.580
In fact, I think we'll ask them as they come
up.

00:09:11.580 --> 00:09:12.890
Put them on the spot.

00:09:12.890 --> 00:09:13.890
&gt;&gt;Ian Ni-Lewis: Indeed.

00:09:13.890 --> 00:09:14.890
&gt;&gt;Reto Meier: Very nice.

00:09:14.890 --> 00:09:20.690
So, one of the other comments that we made
that I recall was I think in terms of displaying

00:09:20.690 --> 00:09:23.970
the content, you know, you've got this rich
visual content, it's all about the pictures

00:09:23.970 --> 00:09:27.860
and I think one of the pieces of feedback
we had was to try and make that an even richer

00:09:27.860 --> 00:09:28.860
experience.

00:09:28.860 --> 00:09:32.460
So you've kind of got your full bleed images
with, you know, the descriptive text overlaying

00:09:32.460 --> 00:09:35.270
that to make it sort of more immersive.

00:09:35.270 --> 00:09:37.420
Is that something that you guys are considering?

00:09:37.420 --> 00:09:40.920
Like, in terms of your overall UI, are you
pretty happy with the direction it's going?

00:09:40.920 --> 00:09:45.310
Have you got any plans of making modifications
in that direction?

